  {
    "text": "Loving the <https://joylabz.com/gigahand-dreams|Gigahand Dreams long form interview podcast> atm. It’s a nice intersection between tech/art/education/making, from Jay Silver who is one of the people who created the Makey Makey.\n\nLast <https://youtu.be/FNtS_PjQAjg?si=atCvMTiOPwFGMjZl|interview I watched was with Andy Cavatorta>, who makes these big crazy tech art contraptions eg, <https://andycavatorta.com/gravityharps.html|an instrument for Björk> and a <https://andycavatorta.com/dual.html|5 player pinball machine to teach the ideas behind economics>.\nSome highlights from it:\n• “How to make things you don’t know how to make” - prototype _a lot_! And be relentless about it - “prolific prototyping” and “discovery orientated design”\n• Mouse in a maze types\n    ◦ The specialist - can run one specific maze, really quickly\n    ◦ The generalist - has the fortitude to wander many mazes, but not quickly\n    ◦ The prototyper - can run unfamiliar mazes quickly, solve unfamiliar problems\n• <https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telharmonium|Telharmonium> - the first electronic music streaming service made using giant organs and the telephone switch board\n• He’s created a <https://andycavatorta.com/curriculum.html|curriculum for teaching his prototyping process> that he has developed over the years, and takes you through algos, maths, electronics, physics, using making tools and programming - which sounds amazing! Too bad I ain’t in NYC though.",
